The paper proposes a new framework that combines an autoencoder with a kernel that accounts for missingness patterns in multivariate time series (MTS). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with a classification problem, which suggests that it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to deal with missing data, which could make it relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with clinical measurements, which could make it relevant to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
